olive oil
1 carrot
1 packet broccoli florets
3 clove garlic
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
20 g butter
¾ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 tsp honey
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Grate carrot. Cut any larger broccoli florets in half. Finely chop garlic.
• Discard any liquid from beef strip packaging.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef strips, chermoula spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil.

• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a dash of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Add carrot and half the garlic, and cook, stirring, until softened, 2-3 minutes. Add the water and chicken-style stock powder and bring to the boil. Add couscous, stir to combine.
• Cover with a lid and remove from heat. Set aside until the water has absorbed, 5 minutes.
• Fluff up with a fork.

• Meanwhile, in a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Add broccoli with a splash of water and cook, tossing, until tender, 6-8 minutes.
• Add remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to a bowl.

• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate.
TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• To the couscous, add broccoli, baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar. Season to taste and stir to combine.

• Divide carrot couscous between bowls. Top with Middle Eastern chicken.
• Drizzle over Greek-style yoghurt. Enjoy!